    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27b.6-7_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">6</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Arlington, Minnesota
                        July 20, 1959
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <addrLine>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</addrLine>
                </opener>
                Would you mind very much if I take the liberty of using your name as a literary reference? You are one of the very few qualified people who have seen any evidence of my writing. Since I lack experience, teachers, and editors, I do hope you won't mind. I have applied for a Eugene F. Saxton fellowship (sponsored by Harper & Brothers), and I need three such references. I need and want this fellowship very much for several reasons. If I can't make it this time (their moral and literarcy standards are very high), I shall try again, and perhaps even again. For my own sake, Doctor, I really am determined to accomplish something worth while at least once in my life.
                
                <p>By the way, Willard and the boys and I plan to be in Fairmont on Wednesday, August 19th, perhaps longer. Will<del>a</del>we see you there? We are all very anxious to meet you? While you are in Minnesota, is there a possibility that you might also visit us in our home? We live very modestly, and I know you would be comfortable. Please think about it.</p>
                
                <p>We are looking forward to seeing you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Jessie H. Erickson</signed>
                    <signed>Jessie H. Erickson</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
